HEADWORD: Consulage
<hw>Con"sul*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Com.)</fld>
<def>A duty or tax paid by merchants for the protection of their
commerce by means of a consul in a foreign place.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Consular</ent>⟦br⟧
